<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/489.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The three Receivers having been appointed, Clark should proceed at once
                            to constitution of Receivership. He should, without delay, make
                            remittance of all sums received for the service 1912 loan and make a
                            full report concerning Receivership to National City Bank, New York.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>